  "texts": [
    "In the UK, for example, no LLM-specific regulation exists at the time of writing.",
    "Additionally, providers of foundation models, which LLMs are built on, must also meet their own set of specific obligations.",
    "Where LLMs are used for reporting purposes, the Technical Actuarial Standards (TASs) reporting principles must be complied with, and any use of an LLM for actuarial work must comply with all TASs, including validation standards.",
    "27 Whilst AI regulation is in development and becoming more readily available, many feel that AI regulation in reporting may be \"too slow to materialise\" (Bodanis, 2023).",
    "Given the principles-based pro-innovation approach in the UK, some feel that specific guidance on the use of LLMs, particularly for reporting, is required, even if regulation may not be feasible (Bodanis, 2023)."
